{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"de219a04-9b89-4e98-9747-6de2782ce733","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`** to benefit from hot reload.\n\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-runs tests automatically when you save a file.\n- **`dotnet watch run`** — for applications, not test projects.\n\nSince your project is a test project, use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` are one-shot commands — they don't watch for file changes. The `dotnet watch` wrapper is what enables hot reload / live re-execution.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f6a566b3-26d5-4751-ba51-d0ba1970ec00","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to use hot reload with .NET testing. Let me look at their project to understand the context better.","outputTokens":167,"requestId":"0840:152A04:DEF622:101AF6D:69EAC987"},"id":"84d0ca19-dc6f-47c1-bdc7-8c222f0b65a3","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:38:20.089Z","parentId":"0521b704-1beb-4177-af80-24ceb1c79076"}
